    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="653"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/3028a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Darnels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 5, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>218. Please telegraph briefly with respect to report published in <hi
                        rend="italic">New York Times</hi> today that President Cardenas has decreed
                    nationalization of 350,000 acres of oil lands under lease to Standard Oil of
                    California and Richmond Petroleum Company as part of nationalization of
                    2,000,000 acres of oil territory in Tabasco, Campeche and Chiapas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
